                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371127-name-846" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-846" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-846" type="surname" value="HOWES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-846" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK HOWES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Little White Lion-street. I keep pigeons at the top of my house, fastened in by a trap-door—I fastened that trap-door on the night of the 12th of October, and on the 13th, between twelve and one o'clock in the morning, I missed ten—I went to Thomas Perks, I bird-fancier in Adam-and-Eve-court, and saw six of them—I traced footsteps along the gutter of the house to No. 5, and there found a bell which had been on the pigeon-house door, and there was some fresh pigeon-dirt on the floor—Gagan lived in that house with his mother and father.</p>
